channelDescription:
Hi, I'm Schellea (Shelly), the founder and CEO of Fabulous50s. At 58, I live in Australia, and it brings me immense joy to help women over 50 feel confident, vibrant, and empowered. My passion is to inspire them to embrace who they are and look forward with excitement to the future."

With 40 years of experience as a small business entrepreneur, my journey has encompassed a wide range of fields, including creative design, health, fitness, fashion, and beauty. I am a certified fitness instructor and Neuroathletics coach, specializing in exercise and brain health for older adults. My focus is on helping women maintain vitality, creativity, longevity, and mental sharpness as they age.

I am also a certified life and business coach, meditation and mindset coach, personal stylist, and color consultant. My mission is to help women over 50 thrive in every aspect of their lives, empowering them to live with confidence, purpose, and joy.

I'm here to guide and support you on your journey. xx

comments: I turned 60 this year. Sadly, I have... let myself go. I am 50lbs  overweight, and my blood pressure is through the roof. I have been sedentary for the last year. I want to retake my life back. I don't like living this way. I hardly recognize myself in the mirror. I'm going to do this. I believe your videos can help. Thank you.

I do one of your workouts daily. It has been a great way to start my day and I find your warmth and personality make it so enjoyable. I would never have thought I could enjoy a workout, but here I am at 57 years old, getting fit and losing weight. 60 lbs down in 9 months, and maybe a little more to come. Thank you!
Great workout thank you. I am 73 and just getting started after many years of sitting in an office and not much exercise.
Your upper body work out really helps with my scoliosis

I can not thankyou enough for these videos. I have been overweight most of my life, trying all sorts of food changes with no great success. While I have never loved exercise I have tried many different forms over the years but because it never shifted any weight I would give up as I also have had a lot of muscles and joint pain from a range of issues. Most of these issues, of course, stem from not loving myself but it has taken awhile to realise that. Anyway all of this is why I am so grateful for you and your videos, they are so filled with love and positivity, having different durations and body options means I can choose ones that fit how my body is feeling each day and really, for the first time in my life I actually get that post exercise buzz that people speak about. You are warm and kind and uplifting and have helped me find some joy in moving my body. Merry Christmas and much love 💜🙏
